other_tests.findings: Numerous hypodensities scattered throughout the liver, the largest is a 1.4 cm hypodensity in segment VII compatible with a simple hepatic cyst. The appendix measures up to 1.4 cm and has a hyperemic and thickened wall with significant periappendiceal fat stranding. No evidence of rupture, free air or organized fluid collections. Lung bases demonstrated subsegmental and segmental atelectasis. No suspicious lytic or sclerotic lesions.
